name: sunkhaze-meadows-national-wildlife-refuge-carlton-pond-national-wildlife-refuge-annual-nar-f3429
notes: This annual narrative report for Sunhaze Meadows NWR and Carlton Pond WPA outlines activities and accomplishments during the 2001 fiscal year. The report begins with an introduction to the Refuge. Highlights and weather conditions are summarized for the year. Information about monitoring and studies- including surveys and censuses and studies and investigations- is provided next. Habitat restoration and management projects are also covered; activities include wetland restoration, water level management, grazing/mowing/haying, forest management, and fire management. Fish and wildlife management are discussed next with emphasis on nest structures. Coordination activities, such as interagency coordination and tribal coordination, are outlined. The resource protection section provides an update on law enforcement, wildfire preparedness, permits, water rights, cultural resource management, and land acquisition support. Information about public education and recreation is given including visitor services and outreach. Finally, comprehensive management planning and general administration are discussed in the Refuge planning and administration section.
